# Patch for /etc/systemd/system/chad-backend.service
# Adds OnFailure= directive routing failures to chad-service-alert@.service
# AND closes PORT-BINDING-1 by switching uvicorn --host from 0.0.0.0 to 127.0.0.1.
# Applied via Channel 1 install runbook (see ops/runbooks/INSTALL_chad_service_alert_template_2026-05-27.md)
# Per CLAUDE.md rule #6: requires explicit operator authorization for the unit edit
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Block 1 — OnFailure directive
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# In the [Unit] section, add:
#
#   OnFailure=chad-service-alert@%n.service
#
# %n expands to the failed unit's full name (chad-backend.service)
# at the time of failure, which becomes the %i in the templated alert unit.
#
# No other lines in the [Unit] section should be modified.
# A backup of the unit file must be taken before this patch is applied:
#   sudo cp /etc/systemd/system/chad-backend.service \
#     /etc/systemd/system/chad-backend.service.bak.2026-05-27
#
# After the edit:
#   sudo systemctl daemon-reload
# (the OnFailure directive activates on the next natural failure)
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Block 2 — Port binding (PORT-BINDING-1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Additionally, in the ExecStart line, change the uvicorn --host argument
# from 0.0.0.0 to 127.0.0.1.
#
# Before:
#   ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/chad_finale/venv/bin/uvicorn chad.dashboard.api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 9618
# After:
#   ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/chad_finale/venv/bin/uvicorn chad.dashboard.api:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 9618
#
# This closes PORT-BINDING-1 for port 9618. The nginx reverse proxy at
# chadtrades.com remains the only external surface for this backend.
#
# If the live ExecStart line in the unit file uses different exact flags
# (different module path, additional --workers, etc.), the operator must
# adapt the patch during install. The patch documents intent, not a literal
# sed substitution.
#
# The ExecStart change only takes effect on the next service restart, which
# remains operator-authorized (CLAUDE.md rule #7).
